Remain where you are.

12
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:44,331
Santiago.

13
00:02:44,414 --> 00:02:46,250
Leave the ball.

14
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:49,962
Leave the stupid ball. Come on.

15
00:02:50,045 --> 00:02:53,090
This is the United States border patrol.

16
00:03:02,724 --> 00:03:06,436
Los Angeles. Ten years later

17
00:03:19,658 --> 00:03:21,577
Santiago.

18
00:03:21,660 --> 00:03:23,203
Stop goofing off.

19
00:03:23,579 --> 00:03:25,455
Load up the truck.

20
00:03:25,539 --> 00:03:27,666
Right now.

21
00:03:43,098 --> 00:03:45,100
He's so hot.

22
00:04:19,468 --> 00:04:21,803
Santiago. Where have you been?

23
00:04:23,305 --> 00:04:24,806
We're already one down.

24
00:04:24,890 --> 00:04:26,099
Only one?

25
00:04:26,183 --> 00:04:27,768
How's the diet going?

26
00:04:27,851 --> 00:04:29,102
What are you doing?

27
00:04:29,186 --> 00:04:30,729
I don't want anybody hurt.

28
00:04:30,812 --> 00:04:32,731
No shin pads. No game. Get off.

29
00:05:36,962 --> 00:05:38,797
See you.

30
00:05:58,108 --> 00:06:00,110
Hey.

31
00:06:02,696 --> 00:06:05,282
How did you do? You play well?

32
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:09,953
Well. We won 4-2. Scored a couple.
Should have got another one.

33
00:06:10,037 --> 00:06:11,580
In Spanish.

34
00:06:11,663 --> 00:06:13,457
What's the deal with Dad?

35
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:16,043
He wants to buy a truck of his own.

36
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:17,628
Why?

37
00:06:17,711 --> 00:06:20,672
So you can work for yourselves.

38
00:06:20,756 --> 00:06:23,050
Munez and son. Eh?

39
00:06:23,133 --> 00:06:25,677
That's what he wants for us?

40
00:06:25,761 --> 00:06:27,971
- There's always plan B.
- Which one is that?

41
00:06:28,055 --> 00:06:31,058
The American Dream.
We win the lottery.

42
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:35,145
What happened?

43
00:06:35,229 --> 00:06:36,647
He wants too much.

44
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:40,108
Too bad.

45
00:06:42,444 --> 00:06:45,072
You have to eat something.

46
00:06:46,198 --> 00:06:47,074
Hey.

47
00:06:52,955 --> 00:06:57,334
Hey. Boss. I've been a busboy now
for six months. Why can't I be a waiter?

48
00:06:57,417 --> 00:07:00,295
This Chinese restaurant.
You're not Chinese.

49
00:07:00,379 --> 00:07:02,840
So? This is America.
You're American. I'm American.

50
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:06,635
- You have green card?
- If I had one. Could I be a waiter?

51
00:07:06,718 --> 00:07:08,804
No. You're not Chinese.

52
00:07:48,677 --> 00:07:51,346
Tommy. Hold your position.

53
00:07:51,430 --> 00:07:53,891
Tommy. You're supposed
to be on the wing.

54
00:07:53,974 --> 00:07:56,268
It's not the Cup Final.
He's seven years old.

55
00:07:56,351 --> 00:07:58,145
You're never too young. Val.

56
00:07:58,228 --> 00:08:00,856
To be honest. I don't think
Tom's that into soccer.

57
00:08:00,939 --> 00:08:02,941
That's b... Oh.

58
00:08:03,901 --> 00:08:05,068
Go.

59
00:08:05,152 --> 00:08:08,113
- Hey. Watch out.
- Go on. Tom.

60
00:08:13,827 --> 00:08:15,996
Thanks.

61
00:08:38,519 --> 00:08:41,188
- He's quite a player.
- Yes. He is.

62
00:08:42,606 --> 00:08:46,693
- Did you teach him to do that?
- God taught him.

63
00:08:51,031 --> 00:08:54,243
He doesn't look right.
His balance is all wrong.

64
00:08:54,326 --> 00:08:56,662
Doesn't look up enough.

65
00:08:56,745 --> 00:08:58,455
Doesn't lift his legs high enough.

66
00:08:58,539 --> 00:09:01,542
That's what all the other teams think.

67
00:09:05,087 --> 00:09:07,756
Then that happens.

68
00:09:17,307 --> 00:09:19,351
Well played. Son.

69
00:09:19,434 --> 00:09:21,562
Do you ever play professional?

70
00:09:21,645 --> 00:09:27,901
Well... pro teams go for college kids and...
none of us went to college.

71
00:09:27,985 --> 00:09:31,196
- When's your next game?
- Saturday.

72
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:35,325
There's someone I bumped into
on the plane on the way over here.

73
00:09:35,409 --> 00:09:38,370
I want him to see you play.
He's a sports agent.

74
00:09:38,453 --> 00:09:41,498
I'm serious. I think you're worth it. Son.

75
00:09:41,582 --> 00:09:43,834
Listen. No offence.
But I need to get to work.

76
00:09:43,917 --> 00:09:46,420
I used to play a bit myself.

77
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:49,673
- Yeah? Where?
- England.

78
00:09:49,756 --> 00:09:53,093
I was a scout too.
I know what I'm talking about.

79
00:09:53,177 --> 00:09:56,013
- England?
- What's your name. Son?

80
00:09:56,096 --> 00:09:59,141
- Santiago Munez.
- Glen Foy.

81
00:10:02,686 --> 00:10:05,522
I'll see you Saturday. Santiago.

82
00:10:12,571 --> 00:10:14,573
Man.

83
00:10:20,537 --> 00:10:23,665
Movie stars have agents.

84
00:10:23,749 --> 00:10:26,460
What's an agent
supposed to do with you?

85
00:10:27,336 --> 00:10:28,670
Do you know something?

86
00:10:28,754 --> 00:10:31,006
Your boy's really good.
He could be a star.

87
00:10:31,089 --> 00:10:33,425
Don't you get it?

88
00:10:33,509 --> 00:10:36,220
There are two types of people
in this world.

89
00:10:36,428 --> 00:10:38,639
Those that live in big houses

90
00:10:38,722 --> 00:10:40,807
and people like us.

91
00:10:40,891 --> 00:10:44,436
Who cut their lawns
and wash their cars.

92
00:10:46,063 --> 00:10:48,524
That could change
if I become a professional player.

93
00:10:49,566 --> 00:10:50,817
What are you saying?

94
00:10:50,901 --> 00:10:53,737
You play in a park with a bunch of guys

95
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:55,447
who work in a car wash.

96
00:10:55,531 --> 00:11:03,372
I don't know. Meet this guy and
everything could change. For the better.

97
00:11:03,455 --> 00:11:07,709
I know how to make things better.

98
00:11:07,793 --> 00:11:11,630
We buy a truck.
We make our own business.

99
00:11:12,047 --> 00:11:14,508
The rest is rubbish.

100
00:11:16,051 --> 00:11:18,303
Another beer.

101
00:11:23,809 --> 00:11:29,690
Baseball. Tennis. Soccer. Basketball.
All at the touch of a button.

102
00:11:29,773 --> 00:11:34,027
Experience the thrill of the game from
the comfort of your home environment.

103
00:11:34,111 --> 00:11:36,947
- Barry. Is this a good moment?
- No time like the present.

104
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:40,659
So he's a young Mexican kid
from the barrio.

105
00:11:41,702 --> 00:11:45,038
He dazzled me. I tell you. Barry.
As you know. I don't dazzle easily.

106
00:11:45,122 --> 00:11:48,584
The last time was a young kid
called Jermain Defoe.

107
00:11:48,667 --> 00:11:53,672
- I'd rather not talk about that. Glen.
- So he's playing on Saturday afternoon.

108
00:11:53,755 --> 00:11:55,465
Some college downtown.

109
00:11:55,549 --> 00:11:58,635
Right. Tell me exactly where it is
and I'll be there 110%.

110
00:11:58,719 --> 00:12:01,597
- Glad to hear it.
- Oh. Hello. Now.

111
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:05,017
Why don't you knock yourself out
and help yourself to finger food?

112
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:08,145
Probably don't do sashimi in Gateshead.
Do they. Mate?

113
00:12:08,228 --> 00:12:10,522
See you later.
Yes. Bruv.

114
00:12:10,606 --> 00:12:13,025
- Would you like some sashimi?
- I'm in LA.

115
00:12:42,471 --> 00:12:45,057
Whoo. Come on. Santiago.

116
00:13:02,324 --> 00:13:04,326
Come on. Back.

117
00:13:17,589 --> 00:13:19,842
Val. Let me use your phone.

118
00:13:22,177 --> 00:13:24,346
Yo.

119
00:13:24,429 --> 00:13:27,182
Glen. Glen. Mate.

120
00:13:27,266 --> 00:13:30,894
Glen. I'm not a dickhead.
I didn't forget. No.

121
00:13:30,978 --> 00:13:35,190
I'm in a business meeting. Bruv. I'm in
a meeting. I'm in a meeting all morning.

122
00:13:35,274 --> 00:13:40,779
Yeah. Sorry. Listen. Mate. Do us a favour.
Can you send me a tape of your boy?

123
00:13:40,863 --> 00:13:43,782
Glen. Glen. GI...

124
00:13:47,452 --> 00:13:49,454
Pillock.

125
00:14:00,382 --> 00:14:02,551
Goal. Yes.

126
00:14:07,055 --> 00:14:09,474
Yeah. Come on. Come on.

127
00:14:25,324 --> 00:14:27,451
Hey. Grandma.

128
00:14:29,244 --> 00:14:31,580
Santiago. Well played. Son. Well done.

129
00:14:31,663 --> 00:14:34,124
Thank you. Thank you.
This is my little brother.

130
00:14:34,208 --> 00:14:37,503
- Hello. How are you? Pleased to meet you.
- And this is my grandma.

131
00:14:37,586 --> 00:14:39,922
- This is my daughter Val.
- Hi.

132
00:14:40,005 --> 00:14:42,007
So you are the agent?

133
00:14:42,090 --> 00:14:44,801
No. No. No. No.
This man arranged for the agent to come.

134
00:14:44,885 --> 00:14:49,640
And he didn't. I'm afraid.
He's... you know. He's too busy.

135
00:14:49,723 --> 00:14:52,726
So he'll come to the next game?

136
00:14:52,809 --> 00:14:55,395
No. No. I'm afraid he can't.

137
00:14:55,479 --> 00:14:58,941
He's flying back to England tomorrow.
So am I.

138
00:14:59,024 --> 00:15:02,319
Look at that.
Maybe the old man is right.

139
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:05,239
You dare to dream. Get screwed.

140
00:15:06,949 --> 00:15:09,576
Thanks anyway.

141
00:15:27,970 --> 00:15:31,223
- Hello. Who is this?
- This is Glen Foy.

142
00:15:31,306 --> 00:15:34,351
Glen Foy? Do I know you. Mr Foy?

143
00:15:34,434 --> 00:15:39,022
Uh... Well. I was one of your scouts
when you first took over.

144
00:15:39,106 --> 00:15:44,403
You fired me. Actually. Well. You brought in
the new regime. I don't hold it against you.

145
00:15:44,486 --> 00:15:49,283
Oh. You don't? So why are you calling me
at half past three in the morning?

146
00:15:49,366 --> 00:15:52,119
Sorry. I'm in California.

147
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:58,458
I've just seen a young player.
I think he's a remarkable talent.

148
00:16:01,336 --> 00:16:05,090
- Who does he play for?
- Oh. Just local league. Kickabout stuff.

149
00:16:05,174 --> 00:16:10,345
The point is. I'm on a plane home tomorrow
and I want you to make me a promise.

150
00:16:10,429 --> 00:16:14,725
If he turns up on your doorstep.
Will you see him?

151
00:16:14,808 --> 00:16:18,812
- You want me to promise you this. Right?
- Aye.

152
00:16:18,896 --> 00:16:23,150
Just give him a run out.
That's all I'm asking.

153
00:16:23,233 --> 00:16:25,611
If I say yes. Can I go back to sleep?

154
00:16:26,195 --> 00:16:28,447
Yes. Mr Dornhelm.

155
00:16:28,530 --> 00:16:30,532
Then yes. Mr Foy.

156
00:16:42,628 --> 00:16:44,671
- Santiago.
- Hey.

157
00:16:45,297 --> 00:16:48,383
- How are you doing?
- Fine. Thank you. Why are you here?

158
00:16:48,467 --> 00:16:51,261
Your coach told me where to find you.

159
00:16:51,386 --> 00:16:53,472
Who's this?

160
00:16:53,555 --> 00:16:56,016
The man from England
who watched me play football.

161
00:16:56,099 --> 00:17:00,062
If you get yourself to England.
Newcastle United will give you a trial.

162
00:17:00,145 --> 00:17:02,189
Newcastle United?

163
00:17:02,272 --> 00:17:05,359
- That's a big club.
- A very big club.

164
00:17:05,442 --> 00:17:07,861
What is this bullshit?

165
00:17:08,862 --> 00:17:12,157
You think you are going to
play football in England?

166
00:17:13,116 --> 00:17:15,410
He thinks I'm good enough.

167
00:17:15,494 --> 00:17:18,580
Why you fill him with ideas like this?

168
00:17:18,664 --> 00:17:21,166
Who the hell do you think you are?

169
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:26,630
And you. Why don't you keep your feet on
the ground instead of your head in the sky?

170
00:17:33,011 --> 00:17:35,597
It's a big thing you ask. Senor.

171
00:17:35,681 --> 00:17:40,018
He's supposed to fly halfway
across the world on something you say?

172
00:17:40,102 --> 00:17:45,399
The manager's made me a promise.
He'll give him a trial. The rest is up to him.

173
00:17:45,482 --> 00:17:48,402
- Look in my eyes and answer me this.
- Grandma.

174
00:17:48,485 --> 00:17:51,321
Can Santi make it as a professional?

175
00:17:51,405 --> 00:17:53,782
Aye. I believe he can.

176
00:17:53,866 --> 00:17:57,995
Dad. We've gotta go. If the freeway's busy.
You're gonna miss your flight.

177
00:17:58,078 --> 00:18:01,540
Here's my card.
It's all my numbers.

178
00:18:01,623 --> 00:18:03,709
Think about it. Give me a ring.

179
00:18:03,792 --> 00:18:05,878
It's good to meet you.

180
00:18:06,879 --> 00:18:08,881
Good to see you.

181
00:18:41,497 --> 00:18:43,874
You got enough?

182
00:18:45,959 --> 00:18:50,172
- Enough what?
- Everyone knows the money's in the boot.

183
00:18:50,255 --> 00:18:52,591
So are you going?

184
00:18:53,550 --> 00:18:57,179
- Grandma thinks I should.
- What does Dad think?

185
00:18:57,262 --> 00:18:59,431
I haven't asked him.

186
00:18:59,515 --> 00:19:01,517
How far away is England?

187
00:19:02,267 --> 00:19:04,269
Right now?

188
00:19:06,730 --> 00:19:09,191
400 bucks too far.

189
00:19:09,274 --> 00:19:11,360
Go back to sleep.

190
00:19:11,443 --> 00:19:12,611
Now.

191
00:19:35,133 --> 00:19:36,552
There?

192
00:20:00,742 --> 00:20:02,744
Thanks.

193
00:20:25,184 --> 00:20:27,227
How could you do this. Dad?

194
00:20:27,311 --> 00:20:29,396
I paid 4500 for the truck.

195
00:20:29,479 --> 00:20:31,815
I took 1200 of yours.

196
00:20:31,899 --> 00:20:34,193
But I'm giving you half the business.

197
00:20:34,776 --> 00:20:36,320
That's a good deal.

198
00:20:36,403 --> 00:20:37,613
You stole that money.

199
00:20:37,696 --> 00:20:39,114
Stay out of this. Mother.

200
00:20:39,198 --> 00:20:41,116
You knew what it was for.

201
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:44,536
- Two more weeks and I have enough.
- For what?

202
00:20:44,620 --> 00:20:46,747
To chase a stupid dream?

203
00:20:47,748 --> 00:20:52,336
Big-time ballplayer in England.
Come on. It's bullshit.

204
00:20:53,253 --> 00:20:56,173
And when you fail. How are you
gonna come back with no papers?

205
00:20:56,256 --> 00:21:00,177
One chance. And you think I should
just give it up for what you do?

206
00:21:00,260 --> 00:21:03,347
What I do is take care of my family.

207
00:21:03,430 --> 00:21:08,352
In Mexico. I work construction.
At night. I clean up in a brothel.

208
00:21:08,435 --> 00:21:11,104
But I save enough to bring us to America.

209
00:21:11,188 --> 00:21:14,608
And when your mother walk out on us...
No. When she walk out.

210
00:21:14,691 --> 00:21:17,194
- I hold this family together.
- Leave her out of this.

211
00:21:17,277 --> 00:21:21,365
I make enough for this house
and now we have our own business.

212
00:21:21,448 --> 00:21:25,077
That's how things get better.
That's how you measure a man's life.

213
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:27,704
It's your life.

214
00:21:29,456 --> 00:21:32,084
Not mine.

215
00:21:52,604 --> 00:21:54,147
Gavin.

216
00:21:57,276 --> 00:21:59,278
Gavin. Gavin.

217
00:22:03,448 --> 00:22:08,412
Ladies and gentlemen.
This is a very good day for the club.

218
00:22:08,495 --> 00:22:10,706
Gavin is a very gifted player

219
00:22:10,789 --> 00:22:15,085
and should fit in very well
with our set-up here at St James' Park.

220
00:22:15,169 --> 00:22:19,840
I'm very pleased to present him... with this.

221
00:22:26,430 --> 00:22:28,515
Winning the league's out of sight. Erik.

222
00:22:28,599 --> 00:22:32,102
What are your realistic goals
for the rest of the season?

223
00:22:32,186 --> 00:22:37,024
Finishing in the first four and qualifying for
Europe. It's essential for a club like this.

224
00:22:37,107 --> 00:22:41,987
To do that. You're gonna have to take
maximum points from your next games.

225
00:22:42,070 --> 00:22:45,240
Look. The club has had
some problems lately. Yeah.

226
00:22:45,324 --> 00:22:47,326
But...

227
00:22:47,993 --> 00:22:50,621
I'm here now. Yeah.

228
00:22:51,538 --> 00:22:56,293
And I'm not in it for fame
or money or anything like that.

229
00:22:56,376 --> 00:22:58,837
I like to win matches.

230
00:22:58,921 --> 00:23:02,007
So maximum points
shouldn't be a problem.

231
00:23:02,090 --> 00:23:03,675
Eh. Boss?

232
00:23:42,381 --> 00:23:43,924
Where's your father?

233
00:23:44,007 --> 00:23:46,385
He's gone to get a part for the truck.

234
00:23:46,468 --> 00:23:47,928
Good.

235
00:23:48,011 --> 00:23:50,055
He doesn't have to hear this.

236
00:23:53,684 --> 00:23:56,520
Train ticket to San Diego.

237
00:23:58,355 --> 00:24:01,191
Bus ticket to Mexico City.

238
00:24:02,860 --> 00:24:04,486
Mexico City?

239
00:24:04,570 --> 00:24:06,029
Yes.

240
00:24:06,113 --> 00:24:09,241
You can't fly to London
from Los Angeles.

241
00:24:09,992 --> 00:24:12,286
You're illegal.

242
00:24:12,911 --> 00:24:14,788
This is your ticket.

243
00:24:14,872 --> 00:24:18,041
It's dated one week from now.

244
00:24:18,292 --> 00:24:20,127
Grandma. How did you pay for this?

245
00:24:22,504 --> 00:24:26,925
I've worked all my life.
I have savings.

246
00:24:27,885 --> 00:24:29,595
What did you sell?

247
00:24:29,845 --> 00:24:30,804
What did you hock?

248
00:24:33,724 --> 00:24:36,852
Old things. From the past.

249
00:24:37,811 --> 00:24:40,522
So now do I get a room to myself?

250
00:24:40,606 --> 00:24:42,399
Come here.

251
00:24:44,234 --> 00:24:46,862
Who's gonna help with your homework?
You won't do it.

252
00:24:46,945 --> 00:24:48,697
He'll do it.

253
00:24:48,780 --> 00:24:53,202
Take a shower before you leave.
You smell real bad.

254
00:24:53,285 --> 00:24:56,288
- Am I leaving tonight?
- Sure.

255
00:24:56,371 --> 00:24:58,499
Before your father gets home.

256
00:25:00,834 --> 00:25:03,921
When your mother walked out on us.

257
00:25:04,004 --> 00:25:08,800
I promised God I'd do everything
to help you boys follow your dreams.

258
00:25:13,263 --> 00:25:16,225
You deserve this chance. Santiago.

259
00:25:22,564 --> 00:25:24,566
Take it.

260
00:25:46,338 --> 00:25:49,967
Passengers making
connecting flights from Mexico

261
00:25:50,050 --> 00:25:53,554
should proceed to gate 14.

262
00:25:53,637 --> 00:25:56,723
- Purpose of your visit?
- Excuse me?

263
00:25:56,807 --> 00:26:00,310
- Business or pleasure?
- Business.

264
00:26:01,895 --> 00:26:05,399
I play... I play soccer... football.

265
00:26:05,482 --> 00:26:08,861
I hope to. For Newcastle United.

266
00:26:11,113 --> 00:26:13,448
One moment.

267
00:26:16,535 --> 00:26:19,454
This young man wants to play
for your team. Mr Henderson.

268
00:26:19,538 --> 00:26:21,623
Newcastle?

269
00:26:21,707 --> 00:26:23,167
Yes. Sir.

270
00:26:23,250 --> 00:26:26,461
Need all the help we can get.

271
00:26:28,839 --> 00:26:30,841
Glen. Phone.

272
00:26:35,470 --> 00:26:37,222
Hello.

273
00:26:37,306 --> 00:26:39,391
Who?

274
00:26:39,474 --> 00:26:40,767
Santiago.

275
00:26:41,310 --> 00:26:43,061
You're in England? Where?

276
00:26:43,145 --> 00:26:45,564
Uh... Somewhere in London.

277
00:26:45,647 --> 00:26:47,649
So. Glen...

278
00:26:48,358 --> 00:26:50,194
how do I get to Newcastle?

279
00:27:29,650 --> 00:27:31,860
Hey. How's it going?

280
00:27:31,944 --> 00:27:36,240
Why didn't you call me from LA?
Let me know you were coming?

281
00:27:36,323 --> 00:27:38,992
- Is it OK that I'm here?
- Oh. No. No. It's fine.

282
00:27:39,076 --> 00:27:42,955
Just caught me a bit off guard. That's all.

283
00:27:45,123 --> 00:27:48,168
Well. You'd best stay with me
till you get settled.

284
00:27:48,252 --> 00:27:50,838
- OK.
- Welcome to the Toon.

285
00:27:52,381 --> 00:27:54,633
- What is that?
- It's where the Geordies live.

286
00:27:54,716 --> 00:27:58,804
- What is a Geordie?
- Someone that lives in the Toon.

287
00:27:58,887 --> 00:28:01,056
You've a lot to learn. Bonny lad.

288
00:28:01,139 --> 00:28:04,351
<i>You mean toons. Like Looney Tunes
and stuff? Like Bugs Bunny?</i>

289
00:28:25,706 --> 00:28:27,708
Thank you.

290
00:28:29,168 --> 00:28:31,503
- You live here alone?
- Aye.

291
00:28:31,587 --> 00:28:34,173
Well. My daughter you met.

292
00:28:34,882 --> 00:28:40,095
- Do you have a wife?
- She died a couple of years ago - cancer.

293
00:28:42,723 --> 00:28:44,933
I'm sorry.

294
00:28:49,062 --> 00:28:51,481
My grandma...

295
00:28:51,565 --> 00:28:53,692
She sent you this.

296
00:28:53,775 --> 00:28:55,777
Oh. It's...

297
00:28:56,695 --> 00:28:59,698
She has it since she's a little girl.

298
00:29:01,867 --> 00:29:04,661
I'm not much of a Catholic. Mind.

299
00:29:04,745 --> 00:29:07,164
She thinks you're a good man. So...

300
00:29:11,585 --> 00:29:14,379
Santiago. Your dinner's ready.

301
00:29:14,463 --> 00:29:16,465
Santiago.

302
00:31:10,579 --> 00:31:12,873
I thought you worked in football.

303
00:31:12,956 --> 00:31:16,919
Not any more. I was finished a while back.
Like some of these cars.

304
00:31:17,002 --> 00:31:20,964
- You fix 'em?
- Aye. I fix them. Restore them.

305
00:31:21,048 --> 00:31:26,345
Listen. There'll not be anyone
at the club till ten o'clock.

306
00:31:26,428 --> 00:31:30,349
So why don't you get yourself something
to eat? Some breakfast or something?

307
00:31:30,432 --> 00:31:33,185
- Yeah.
- Do you have any money?

308
00:31:33,268 --> 00:31:35,771
No. But I'm OK.

309
00:31:39,900 --> 00:31:42,069
- No. I can't.
- It's OK.

310
00:31:43,028 --> 00:31:45,697
Take it. Turn right.

311
00:31:45,781 --> 00:31:47,783
Just for now.

312
00:31:50,118 --> 00:31:52,496
Here. Mate. Watch the ball.

313
00:31:52,579 --> 00:31:54,581
Oh. No.

314
00:32:00,629 --> 00:32:04,132
Hey. Mister. Can we have wor ball back?

315
00:32:06,218 --> 00:32:09,596
- Quite tasty.
- Aye. If you work in a circus.

316
00:32:09,680 --> 00:32:13,141
- I'm done. Sorry. Here.
- Nice one.

317
00:32:14,101 --> 00:32:16,728
I hear some players
have a problem with Gavin Harris.

318
00:32:16,812 --> 00:32:18,981
- Divvent like his attitude.
- Aye.

319
00:32:19,064 --> 00:32:22,234
Well. Three clubs in five years
should tell you something.

320
00:32:22,317 --> 00:32:25,279
I think he's better playing on the inside.

321
00:32:25,362 --> 00:32:27,573
If he's in a mood. He gets lost out wide.

322
00:32:27,656 --> 00:32:29,533
Aye. Right enough. Like.

323
00:32:31,451 --> 00:32:33,704
What are you looking at?

324
00:32:33,787 --> 00:32:36,540
Sorry. But you're
talking about soccer. Right?

325
00:32:36,623 --> 00:32:39,543
- No.
- Football?

326
00:32:39,626 --> 00:32:42,713
Oh. Aye. Yeah.
That's all there is to talk about.

327
00:32:42,796 --> 00:32:44,882
- Where are you from. Son?
- Los Angeles.

328
00:32:44,965 --> 00:32:49,261
Oh. Aye? You know Charlize Theron?
She's a cracker. Like.

329
00:32:49,344 --> 00:32:53,849
- What are you doing up here?
- I have a tryout for Newcastle United.

330
00:32:53,932 --> 00:32:57,311
- A trial. Like? Howay.
- Are you serious. Lad?

331
00:32:57,394 --> 00:32:59,396
Yeah. Yeah. Maybe today. Actually.

332
00:32:59,479 --> 00:33:02,608
You wanna lay off the black pudding. Son.

333
00:33:04,568 --> 00:33:08,739
- What is it exactly?
- You don't want to know.

334
00:33:10,491 --> 00:33:14,536
Football's a religion here. London has any
number of teams. Same in the Midlands.

335
00:33:14,620 --> 00:33:19,041
Manchester. You've got two. Liverpool.
You've got two. Glasgow's got two.

336
00:33:19,124 --> 00:33:21,835
Up here. Though. It's just the Toon.

337
00:33:23,879 --> 00:33:25,714
There she is.

338
00:33:38,894 --> 00:33:42,397
- Is that the manager?
- Erik Dornhelm. Mr Dornhelm.

339
00:33:42,481 --> 00:33:44,733
He can be intimidating.
Look him in the eye.

340
00:33:44,816 --> 00:33:47,903
I don't think my look will make a difference.

341
00:33:47,986 --> 00:33:53,075
- It'll be my feet.
- Mr Dornhelm. Excuse me. Glen Foy.

342
00:33:53,158 --> 00:33:55,661
This is the young man
I was telling you about.

343
00:33:55,744 --> 00:33:58,413
- Hi.
- He's from Los Angeles.

344
00:33:59,706 --> 00:34:01,917
Santiago Munez.

345
00:34:03,168 --> 00:34:05,170
When was this?

346
00:34:06,171 --> 00:34:08,340
When I phoned you
in the middle of the night.

347
00:34:08,423 --> 00:34:10,634
You promised to give him a trial.

348
00:34:10,717 --> 00:34:13,262
Yes. One minute. Please.

349
00:34:14,596 --> 00:34:17,224
Like that?
Score a hat trick. You can have it.

350
00:34:17,307 --> 00:34:22,145
I'm sure you have a watch and I'm
absolutely sure it's an expensive one.

351
00:34:22,229 --> 00:34:24,064
What time does it say?

352
00:34:24,147 --> 00:34:27,901
Sorry. Boss. I was dropping a shirt off
for a sick kid in hospital.

353
00:34:27,985 --> 00:34:31,822
The PR people should have had a camera.
Would have been a really good photo op.

354
00:34:31,905 --> 00:34:38,287
That. I think. Is bullshit. There are six
journalists inside. Waiting for 15 minutes.

355
00:34:38,370 --> 00:34:40,914
Get in there.

356
00:34:40,998 --> 00:34:45,544
- And today. You train with the reserves.
- Oh. F...

357
00:34:48,839 --> 00:34:51,758
- Where do you play?
- Los Angeles.

358
00:34:51,842 --> 00:34:54,136
I meant position.

359
00:34:54,219 --> 00:34:57,723
Yeah. For my team. I play up front.
But I prefer midfield.

360
00:34:57,806 --> 00:35:00,475
That way. I see more of the ball.

361
00:35:05,564 --> 00:35:08,609
Get him over to the training ground.
Let's see what he's got.

362
00:35:08,692 --> 00:35:11,111
Will do. Thank you very much.

363
00:35:20,370 --> 00:35:22,706
Hey. I'll be around.

364
00:35:45,354 --> 00:35:49,233
Oh. You're there.
How are you feeling. Son?

365
00:35:49,316 --> 00:35:53,195
- OK.
- Good. Mal Braithwaite. Club coach.

366
00:35:53,278 --> 00:35:56,782
I've been a friend of Glen's
since he played here. So I'm on your side.

367
00:35:56,865 --> 00:35:58,700
- All right?
- Yeah. Thank you. Sir.

368
00:35:58,784 --> 00:36:01,078
I'm not a sir. I'm a coach.

369
00:36:01,161 --> 00:36:05,624
Sir is the gaffer. That's who's gonna
be watching you today. All right? Fit?

370
00:36:05,707 --> 00:36:07,709
- Yeah.
- Good. Let's go.

371
00:36:10,546 --> 00:36:14,091
Come on. It'll be fine.

372
00:36:15,634 --> 00:36:16,969
Yeah.

373
00:36:20,055 --> 00:36:23,058
- Come on.
- Get up the field.

374
00:36:24,393 --> 00:36:26,937
- Behind you.
- Keep moving it.

375
00:36:27,020 --> 00:36:29,064
Put it square.

376
00:36:29,147 --> 00:36:30,816
Son.

377
00:36:31,859 --> 00:36:33,986
I want you midfield. On the right. OK?

378
00:36:34,069 --> 00:36:36,071
- Gavin... You know who Gavin is?
- No.

379
00:36:36,155 --> 00:36:37,739
- Slot in behind him there.
- OK.

380
00:36:37,823 --> 00:36:40,242
That's the fella. OK?

381
00:36:40,325 --> 00:36:44,246
- Get Adie off.
- Adie. Come off.

382
00:36:46,832 --> 00:36:50,627
OK. Pal. Swap bibs with him.
Do your best.

383
00:36:53,922 --> 00:36:56,717
Hey. Mal. Mal. Who's the muppet?

384
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:59,720
He's from Mexico. Be gentle. Son.

385
00:36:59,803 --> 00:37:02,139
Yeah. I'll look after him.

386
00:37:06,018 --> 00:37:07,644
Hey. Yo. Hey. Yo. Yo.

387
00:37:20,115 --> 00:37:21,992
That's it. Phil.

388
00:37:22,534 --> 00:37:27,247
- How are you. Mal? Bobby. How are you?
- All right. Boss?

389
00:37:27,831 --> 00:37:31,752
Franny. Bring the kid into the game.

390
00:37:44,515 --> 00:37:46,266
Look at me.

391
00:37:48,185 --> 00:37:50,270
Here. Yo. Yo.

392
00:37:51,563 --> 00:37:53,148
Oh. Fuck.

393
00:37:57,194 --> 00:38:00,239
- What? A bit louder. Please.
- Oh. Come on.

394
00:38:01,240 --> 00:38:03,033
Here.

395
00:38:12,292 --> 00:38:15,254
All right. Let me call you back.

396
00:38:49,163 --> 00:38:51,498
Let the kid take it.

397
00:38:57,546 --> 00:38:59,548
Go on. Have a go.

398
00:39:01,008 --> 00:39:03,677
Face up. How many?

399
00:39:11,768 --> 00:39:13,687
Adios. Amigo.

400
00:39:18,108 --> 00:39:20,152
Santiago.

401
00:39:22,321 --> 00:39:25,073
Get yourself a shower.

402
00:40:08,450 --> 00:40:10,994
I don't know. Glen.

403
00:40:11,078 --> 00:40:15,374
My legs wouldn't do
what my brain was telling them.

404
00:40:15,457 --> 00:40:18,669
I'll be better tomorrow. I promise.

405
00:40:18,752 --> 00:40:22,506
There's not gonna be
a tomorrow. Santiago.

406
00:40:26,385 --> 00:40:28,387
Get in the car.

407
00:40:49,449 --> 00:40:53,036
You know. My father believes
people have a place in life.

408
00:40:53,120 --> 00:40:55,622
You work. You feed your family.

409
00:40:55,706 --> 00:40:57,416
You die.

410
00:40:59,459 --> 00:41:02,963
And it's foolish to think otherwise.

411
00:41:12,931 --> 00:41:15,893
- Excuse me. Sir...
- I had a word with the fellow on the door.

412
00:41:15,976 --> 00:41:21,607
He said I could come in and just look
for someone. I won't be a second.

413
00:41:24,401 --> 00:41:28,113
Mr Dornhelm.
Glen Foy from this morning.

414
00:41:28,197 --> 00:41:32,451
Listen. I'm sorry
to interrupt the proceedings.

415
00:41:32,534 --> 00:41:34,786
Have I missed all the boring speeches?

416
00:41:34,870 --> 00:41:38,540
I'm making one of the "boring" speeches.
This distraction is not welcome.

417
00:41:38,624 --> 00:41:41,960
Well. If you'd answered my calls.
I wouldn't be here.

418
00:41:42,044 --> 00:41:46,798
- What do you want?
- Listen. This kid. Santiago Munez.

419
00:41:46,882 --> 00:41:50,469
- Would you like to sit here?
- Sure. Thanks.

420
00:41:50,552 --> 00:41:53,263
Listen. He's grown up
in poverty and hardship

421
00:41:53,347 --> 00:41:56,767
and his only way out
is his skill with the ball.

422
00:41:56,850 --> 00:42:00,437
He's flown 6.000 miles on my say-so.

423
00:42:00,521 --> 00:42:03,065
He's jet-lagged. He's nervous.

424
00:42:03,148 --> 00:42:07,820
You know. He's never seen mud before
and you put him on a pitch like that.

425
00:42:07,903 --> 00:42:11,573
And then you spend
the whole time on your mobile.

426
00:42:11,657 --> 00:42:17,329
- I saw him flat on his ass most of the time.
- Yet there was one moment of magic.

427
00:42:18,705 --> 00:42:21,208
When he took the ball on the bounce.

428
00:42:21,291 --> 00:42:24,628
- Turned Magowan. Took it down.
- I saw it.

429
00:42:27,381 --> 00:42:31,385
Looks good.
Hear they do you well here.

430
00:42:31,468 --> 00:42:33,637
Listen. When I was a scout.

431
00:42:34,555 --> 00:42:37,057
I used to spend the whole time.
On muddy days.

432
00:42:37,140 --> 00:42:41,311
Watching young lads
clogging the shite out of each other.

433
00:42:41,395 --> 00:42:47,109
And just once in a while. There'd be one
that'd come along and lift your heart.

434
00:42:47,192 --> 00:42:49,820
Like this lad.

435
00:42:51,363 --> 00:42:53,699
Just give him a month.

436
00:43:31,570 --> 00:43:34,364
Ah. So you found all my yesterdays?

437
00:43:34,448 --> 00:43:36,533
I was just looking.

438
00:43:37,326 --> 00:43:39,828
My wife made this scrapbook.

439
00:43:39,912 --> 00:43:42,873
You never told me
you were a major-league player.

440
00:43:42,956 --> 00:43:47,127
Aye. Well. Not for as long as I'd have liked.

441
00:43:47,211 --> 00:43:50,506
- Why?
- Got an injury. Did my knee in.

442
00:43:51,465 --> 00:43:55,260
Look at that.
Shorts were shorter. Hair was longer.

443
00:43:55,344 --> 00:43:58,472
Didn't make £8 million a year. Either.

444
00:44:00,182 --> 00:44:02,309
- But you were still heroes.
- Oh. Aye.

445
00:44:02,392 --> 00:44:06,146
Footballers have always been heroes.
Even in my father's day. Earning £8 a week

446
00:44:06,230 --> 00:44:09,775
and working down the mine
at the same time.

447
00:44:12,110 --> 00:44:15,531
- There you go.
- No. I can't accept it. It's too special.

448
00:44:15,614 --> 00:44:17,908
I'm not giving it to you.
Just try it on.

449
00:44:17,991 --> 00:44:21,370
I want to see what you look like
in the black and white.

450
00:44:21,453 --> 00:44:23,914
- What's the point?
- What's the point?

451
00:44:23,997 --> 00:44:26,667
Well. You've got a month's trial.

452
00:44:31,380 --> 00:44:34,049
Better phone your granny again.

453
00:44:45,269 --> 00:44:49,523
Right. Listen up. You lot.
This is Santiago Munez. He's from Mexico.

454
00:44:49,606 --> 00:44:52,192
- No. Los Angeles.
- Los Angeles. Whatever.

455
00:44:52,276 --> 00:44:55,487
Before this day's done.
I want you to let him know who you are.

456
00:44:55,571 --> 00:44:57,823
OK. Right. Let's get to it.

457
00:45:01,660 --> 00:45:03,871
Push it hard. Hard.

458
00:45:07,207 --> 00:45:10,794
Nice one. Franny.
Nice work. Come on.

459
00:45:10,878 --> 00:45:12,796
15.

460
00:45:12,880 --> 00:45:14,464
16.

461
00:45:14,548 --> 00:45:16,675
17.

462
00:45:27,060 --> 00:45:29,062
Come on. Santiago.

463
00:45:39,573 --> 00:45:42,201
- Santi. I've been to Mexico once.
- Did you like it?

464
00:45:42,284 --> 00:45:44,578
Gave me the shits for a week.

465
00:45:57,257 --> 00:45:59,259
One day. Son.

466
00:46:00,093 --> 00:46:02,638
But not today. Come on. Move.

467
00:46:06,141 --> 00:46:08,018
Thank you.

468
00:46:08,644 --> 00:46:12,022
- Do you want to sit down. Please?
- OK.

469
00:46:38,298 --> 00:46:42,219
- It may be a little high.
- Why's that?

470
00:46:42,302 --> 00:46:46,306
Well. 'cause you are so close
and you smell nice.

471
00:46:48,809 --> 00:46:51,228
It's normal.

472
00:46:52,855 --> 00:46:57,192
- Are you the club doctor?
- No. I'm his nurse. He'll examine you soon.

473
00:46:57,276 --> 00:47:00,320
- Did you fill in the paperwork?
- Yeah.

474
00:47:00,404 --> 00:47:04,158
Just a couple of words I didn't understand.

475
00:47:05,701 --> 00:47:08,412
OK. Like what?

476
00:47:09,204 --> 00:47:11,832
Like this one here.

477
00:47:12,416 --> 00:47:15,961
That's "cardiovascular".
It means "heart problems".

478
00:47:16,044 --> 00:47:18,130
Oh. No. No.

479
00:47:18,213 --> 00:47:20,048
And how about that one?

480
00:47:20,132 --> 00:47:26,346
"Respiratory" - do you have any problems
with your lungs or breathing?

481
00:47:26,972 --> 00:47:28,974
Do you?

482
00:47:30,559 --> 00:47:31,894
No.

483
00:47:31,977 --> 00:47:34,605
Do you wanna step on the scales?

484
00:47:40,194 --> 00:47:42,321
Right.

485
00:47:43,155 --> 00:47:46,408
- What's your name?
- Nurse Harmison.

486
00:47:46,492 --> 00:47:49,912
- I mean your first name.
- You don't need to know that.

487
00:47:49,995 --> 00:47:52,789
You don't need to know where I live.
What my star sign is.

488
00:47:52,873 --> 00:47:54,917
Or what I'm doing on Saturday night.

489
00:47:55,000 --> 00:48:00,839
- I'm gonna have to take blood.
- Oh. Man. Really? I don't like needles.

490
00:48:02,216 --> 00:48:05,427
But you have a tattoo.
Or is that a rub-on transfer?

491
00:48:05,511 --> 00:48:08,514
- That was a gang thing.
- You were in a gang?

492
00:48:11,058 --> 00:48:13,060
Not any more.

493
00:48:15,729 --> 00:48:20,108
There's only three ways to get out
of a gang - you get shot. You go to jail. Or...

494
00:48:20,192 --> 00:48:24,238
In my case. You have a grandmother
who kicks some sense into you.

495
00:48:26,073 --> 00:48:28,534
Sorry. Tough guy.

496
