01:10:38,947 --> 01:10:44,244
- I've already got a fare.
- He's first team. Man. Get there ASAP.

736
01:10:44,328 --> 01:10:48,665
Gotta do a detour. Bonny lad.
Celebrity in peril.

737
01:10:58,133 --> 01:11:00,886
You're that kid from LA?
You going to training as well?

738
01:11:00,969 --> 01:11:04,556
- No. I have to get to the station.
- Why?

739
01:11:04,640 --> 01:11:07,309
- I screwed up.
- Tell me about it on the way.

740
01:11:07,392 --> 01:11:10,354
I don't know what
the gaffer will do if I'm late.

741
01:11:18,237 --> 01:11:20,406
So you're Gavin Harris?

742
01:11:21,156 --> 01:11:23,283
- Guilty.
- You're shite.

743
01:11:24,535 --> 01:11:28,205
So I've heard.
Come on. Santi.

744
01:11:28,288 --> 01:11:31,834
With all due respect. Gaffer. Mr Dornhelm.

745
01:11:31,917 --> 01:11:34,962
The club will be making a big mistake
if they let this lad go.

746
01:11:35,045 --> 01:11:37,423
I've played with him.
I've played against him.

747
01:11:37,506 --> 01:11:40,717
I can see he's got it.
So can all of the other lads.

748
01:11:40,801 --> 01:11:44,471
- I mean. Technically...
- What? He's better than you?

749
01:11:47,182 --> 01:11:48,892
Well.

750
01:11:49,893 --> 01:11:52,271
He's in that league.

751
01:11:52,354 --> 01:11:58,026
What happened last night was he lost his
inhaler. He's got asthma. For God's sake.

752
01:11:58,110 --> 01:12:00,529
Is this true?

753
01:12:00,612 --> 01:12:03,282
Yes. Sir. But I tried to hide it.

754
01:12:04,283 --> 01:12:06,910
Lying is a problem.
Asthma is not.

755
01:12:06,994 --> 01:12:09,580
You can get shots.
Medication. Acupuncture.

756
01:12:09,663 --> 01:12:12,750
Didn't your doctor back home
explain this to you?

757
01:12:12,833 --> 01:12:17,129
I don't have a doctor.
All I got is a free clinic in LA.

758
01:12:20,883 --> 01:12:26,805
- People keep pleading your case. Munez.
- All I wanna do is prove them right. Sir.

759
01:12:26,889 --> 01:12:29,349
If you give me the chance.

760
01:12:29,433 --> 01:12:32,478
- You think you deserve it?
- I know I do.

761
01:12:38,609 --> 01:12:40,569
Good.

762
01:12:40,652 --> 01:12:44,073
See the doc.
Tell him about your condition.

763
01:12:44,156 --> 01:12:47,534
Then report for training. All right?

764
01:12:50,871 --> 01:12:53,207
Thank you.

765
01:12:55,042 --> 01:12:56,502
Gavin.

766
01:13:00,047 --> 01:13:02,925
This is a decent thing you did.

767
01:13:03,008 --> 01:13:05,594
Yeah. I do what I can.

768
01:13:08,013 --> 01:13:10,349
Now explain why are you
dressed for discotheque

769
01:13:10,432 --> 01:13:13,143
and 47 minutes late for training?

770
01:13:22,069 --> 01:13:25,864
Reserve Game
Newcastle United V Queens Park Rangers

771
01:13:32,413 --> 01:13:34,248
- Come on.
- You like him?

772
01:13:34,331 --> 01:13:36,333
Yeah.

773
01:13:36,417 --> 01:13:38,877
Go on.

774
01:13:42,506 --> 01:13:46,260
- Stand up. Santi.
- Away you go. Fellas. Away.

775
01:13:46,343 --> 01:13:48,345
Yes. Please.

776
01:13:54,476 --> 01:13:56,687
Yeah.

777
01:14:09,783 --> 01:14:12,077
- Bloody late.
- Got there as quick as I could.

778
01:14:12,161 --> 01:14:14,580
Hughie. Hughie.
Yes. Please. Fella.

779
01:14:14,663 --> 01:14:16,874
No more of that.
That is naughty. OK?

780
01:14:16,957 --> 01:14:19,877
- Away you go.
- He'll think twice about doing you again.

781
01:14:19,960 --> 01:14:23,297
- Thought you didn't like me.
- My sister will be upset if you get hurt.

782
01:14:23,380 --> 01:14:27,092
She thinks you look like Antonio Banderas.

783
01:14:28,302 --> 01:14:31,597
Hey. If you shag her. I'll kill you.

784
01:14:44,985 --> 01:14:46,904
Reserve Game
Newcastle United V Middlesbrough

785
01:15:12,429 --> 01:15:15,891
- Be careful.
- OK. I can't see a thing.

786
01:15:15,974 --> 01:15:18,936
OK. You're almost there. Little step.

787
01:15:19,019 --> 01:15:21,605
Little step down. Right.

788
01:15:22,606 --> 01:15:25,442
Oh. My God. It's amazing.

789
01:15:27,027 --> 01:15:29,405
- Can you believe this?
- No.

790
01:15:29,488 --> 01:15:32,741
A month ago. I said goodbye to the city.
Goodbye to you.

791
01:15:32,825 --> 01:15:35,035
And now I've got a contract.

792
01:15:35,702 --> 01:15:40,082
- And this little apartment.
- How can you afford it. Though?

793
01:15:42,292 --> 01:15:43,794
Gavino.

794
01:15:43,877 --> 01:15:46,004
Say hello to my friend.

795
01:15:46,088 --> 01:15:47,756
Hello.

796
01:15:50,134 --> 01:15:52,970
I didn't say you could bring women here.

797
01:15:53,053 --> 01:15:55,556
Oh. I'm sorry. Shall I go?

798
01:16:00,769 --> 01:16:04,189
<i>- I'm just kidding. Man. Ciao. Bella.
- How's it going?</i>

799
01:16:04,273 --> 01:16:08,736
Oh. Make yourselves at home.
There's finger stuff in the fridge.

800
01:16:08,819 --> 01:16:12,197
Oh. Takeaway pizzas and ladies knickers?

801
01:16:12,823 --> 01:16:16,493
Not hard to figure out his lifestyle. Is it?

802
01:16:16,577 --> 01:16:19,663
He's all right.
He saved my ass. Remember?

803
01:16:19,747 --> 01:16:26,044
- Got a bit of a rep is what I've heard.
- For professionals. Football is our life.

804
01:16:31,800 --> 01:16:35,012
- Good to see you.
- How are you tonight?

805
01:16:36,221 --> 01:16:37,598
Gavin. You all right?

806
01:17:01,622 --> 01:17:04,583
Colin. It's a very good offer.
But just forget about it.

807
01:17:04,666 --> 01:17:07,002
I'll tell you.
'Cause the chairman is a tosser.

808
01:17:07,086 --> 01:17:10,464
The manager knows and says nothing.
Which makes him a bigger tosser.

809
01:17:10,547 --> 01:17:12,549
The players know it.

810
01:17:12,633 --> 01:17:17,304
Yeah. It's all clans and cliques
in the dressing room. Innit. Luv?

811
01:17:17,387 --> 01:17:19,848
- Yeah. Gav.
- Little bit on your nose. Mate.

812
01:17:19,932 --> 01:17:24,228
24-7. mate.
Listen. What's cool and hangs up?

813
01:17:24,311 --> 01:17:26,146
All right. Mate.

814
01:17:26,230 --> 01:17:29,108
- All right. Baz.
- Look at you. Crispy. Mate. How are you?

815
01:17:29,191 --> 01:17:32,194
- Say hello to Santi.
- Heard it's going good. Mate.

816
01:17:32,277 --> 01:17:35,364
Notched a pair for the reserves Saturday.

817
01:17:42,955 --> 01:17:44,623
- Hello.
- Hi. How are you doing?

818
01:17:44,706 --> 01:17:48,460
So. Santi. You got your contract sorted
to the end of the season?

819
01:17:48,544 --> 01:17:53,215
Do you mind if I ask actually
who handled that for you?

820
01:17:53,298 --> 01:17:55,592
- Glen.
- Glen Foy?

821
01:17:55,676 --> 01:17:58,971
- Works in a garage. Bruv.
- Well. It's not actually...

822
01:17:59,054 --> 01:18:03,851
Don't get me wrong. He's a lovely fella.
He used to be an absolute cracking player.

823
01:18:03,934 --> 01:18:08,313
But what does he know
about marketability?

824
01:18:09,189 --> 01:18:11,984
What does he know about endorsements?

825
01:18:12,067 --> 01:18:15,487
You make the first team.
Santi. Next season...

826
01:18:17,239 --> 01:18:19,408
I'll get you a Gap ad.

827
01:18:19,491 --> 01:18:21,660
Crunch.

828
01:18:23,370 --> 01:18:26,331
Hey. Pet. Do you fancy a dance?

829
01:18:26,415 --> 01:18:28,542
Watch out. He's a salsa man.

830
01:18:29,376 --> 01:18:31,336
No. Thank you. Sorry.

831
01:19:06,830 --> 01:19:08,248
Hello.

832
01:19:08,332 --> 01:19:11,794
Santiago? Hey. Bro.
What's going on?

833
01:19:11,877 --> 01:19:13,712
No way.

834
01:19:14,421 --> 01:19:15,881
Papa. It's Santiago.

835
01:19:15,964 --> 01:19:18,008
He wants to talk to you.

836
01:19:20,010 --> 01:19:22,638
Tell him I'm not here.

837
01:19:23,097 --> 01:19:25,099
He can't talk right now. OK?

838
01:19:29,311 --> 01:19:31,855
No problem. Man.

839
01:19:35,776 --> 01:19:37,778
Ey-up. Lads.

840
01:19:38,737 --> 01:19:41,281
Take them up the back pitch. Andy.
Give 'em a stretch.

841
01:19:41,365 --> 01:19:43,492
Kicked me out. Bin-bagged.

842
01:19:43,575 --> 01:19:47,704
- I've got my eye on you. Hughie.
- See you in the showers. Bobby.

843
01:19:50,290 --> 01:19:54,420
- What's up?
- What's up? I just saw the reserve list.

844
01:19:54,503 --> 01:19:57,548
I'm not on the team.
I didn't even make the bench.

845
01:19:57,631 --> 01:19:59,633
I don't get it.

846
01:19:59,716 --> 01:20:02,845
I play where you tell me to play.
I play how you tell me to play.

847
01:20:02,928 --> 01:20:05,556
I didn't drop you. Son.
You're not at my disposal.

848
01:20:05,639 --> 01:20:09,101
- What are you talking about?
- You're playing with that lot.

849
01:20:09,184 --> 01:20:11,728
In London on Saturday.

850
01:20:13,689 --> 01:20:16,024
Santiago.

851
01:20:18,819 --> 01:20:21,822
What are you waiting for?
Come on.

852
01:20:21,905 --> 01:20:24,533
OK. Guys. Let's get to work.

853
01:20:24,616 --> 01:20:26,702
Come on.

854
01:20:56,774 --> 01:20:59,818
Newcastle scraped through
with a win over Chelsea.

855
01:20:59,902 --> 01:21:03,489
But it won't be enough in itself.
Liverpool are breathing down their necks.

856
01:21:03,572 --> 01:21:08,702
And to make it worse. There is a makeshift
look to the Newcastle United line-up today

857
01:21:08,786 --> 01:21:13,373
with all their injury problems. And one
of their substitutes. Santiago Munez.

858
01:21:13,457 --> 01:21:16,293
- Is an unknown quantity.
- He is.

859
01:21:16,376 --> 01:21:18,962
Apparently he was discovered
playing in Los Angeles

860
01:21:19,046 --> 01:21:21,757
by Glen Foy. The ex-Newcastle midfielder.

861
01:21:21,840 --> 01:21:25,260
He's been turning some heads
with his performances in the reserves.

862
01:21:25,344 --> 01:21:27,596
But this is a much. Much higher level.

863
01:21:27,679 --> 01:21:33,519
I just wonder how he will cope
if he does get the nod at some point today.

864
01:21:53,914 --> 01:21:56,500
- What have I missed?
- Not a lot.

865
01:21:57,918 --> 01:22:02,131
- How are you feeling?
- I'll feel better if we get three points.

866
01:22:26,572 --> 01:22:31,410
- He's useless. He's useless.
- Howay. Man. Give him a break.

867
01:22:31,493 --> 01:22:35,289
- Get in there.
- Put a challenge in. Man.

868
01:22:43,881 --> 01:22:46,049
Did you see that?

869
01:22:46,967 --> 01:22:48,260
Come on. Ref.

870
01:22:49,261 --> 01:22:51,263
Munez.

871
01:22:55,684 --> 01:22:58,520
Munez. You're going on.

872
01:22:59,480 --> 01:23:02,149
A bold move.
But in the circumstances.

873
01:23:02,232 --> 01:23:04,318
I don't think he's got much other choice.

874
01:23:04,401 --> 01:23:07,571
And it is now quite a day
for this young man.

875
01:23:07,654 --> 01:23:10,365
This is a chance to show your worth.
Give me your jacket.

876
01:23:10,449 --> 01:23:13,160
Show them what you've got. Son.

877
01:23:16,455 --> 01:23:17,581
Come on.

878
01:23:17,664 --> 01:23:19,666
Who the hell is this?

879
01:23:21,251 --> 01:23:23,420
That's my son.

880
01:23:24,338 --> 01:23:27,382
That's my boy. Santiago.
I'm his father.

881
01:23:27,466 --> 01:23:31,929
If he scores. Like. I'll buy you a pint.
Come on. Son. Sit at the bar.

882
01:23:32,012 --> 01:23:34,014
Come on.

883
01:23:40,145 --> 01:23:42,731
Substitution for Newcastle United.

884
01:23:42,815 --> 01:23:45,359
Coming off. Number 13. Carl Francis.

885
01:23:45,442 --> 01:23:49,196
Being replaced by number 26.
Santiago Munez.

886
01:23:54,201 --> 01:23:56,203
Go on. Yes.

887
01:24:08,549 --> 01:24:11,051
What a great run by Munez.

888
01:24:11,135 --> 01:24:13,720
Brought down. Penalty.

889
01:24:14,763 --> 01:24:16,640
Come on. Boys.

890
01:24:19,226 --> 01:24:21,103
Penalty. Boys. Penalty.

891
01:24:21,186 --> 01:24:26,650
- Down. You.
- I can't watch it if that playboy's taking it.

892
01:24:31,780 --> 01:24:34,032
Just calm it down. All right?

893
01:24:37,369 --> 01:24:39,371
I hate this stuff.

894
01:25:02,436 --> 01:25:05,647
- I'll buy you that pint now. Son.
- It's a little early.

895
01:25:05,731 --> 01:25:09,401
Not in Newcastle. It's not.
Howay. The lads.

896
01:25:10,402 --> 01:25:14,073
Only seconds to go and if it ends like this.

897
01:25:14,156 --> 01:25:18,243
It will be a happy journey back to
the Northeast for the Newcastle players.

898
01:25:26,376 --> 01:25:29,338
- Right. You should lie down. You.
- Aye.

899
01:25:29,421 --> 01:25:31,423
Salsa man.

900
01:25:31,965 --> 01:25:34,093
Munez.

901
01:25:34,176 --> 01:25:38,097
Ah. Beautiful. I know.
Beautiful stuff.

902
01:25:39,348 --> 01:25:41,600
What did you notice
when you won that penalty?

903
01:25:41,683 --> 01:25:45,396
Uh. I noticed... the goal?

904
01:25:45,479 --> 01:25:48,524
You should have noticed two players
in a better position than you.

905
01:25:48,607 --> 01:25:50,901
You don't pass.
You go for glory.

906
01:25:57,241 --> 01:25:59,576
Sven. How are you?

907
01:26:01,161 --> 01:26:05,249
Stop brooding about it. Man.
The gaffer does that to everyone.

908
01:26:05,332 --> 01:26:08,669
You played great.
Everyone saw that. Yeah.

909
01:26:08,752 --> 01:26:10,087
Hey. Hey. Johnny.

910
01:26:10,170 --> 01:26:12,423
- Santiago.
- Hey.

911
01:26:12,506 --> 01:26:14,550
Congratulations. You were amazing.

912
01:26:14,633 --> 01:26:16,718
Oh. Thanks.

913
01:26:16,802 --> 01:26:21,807
My whole family are mad Real Madrid fans.
My grandma. She loves you. Man.

914
01:26:21,890 --> 01:26:26,270
Well. Carry on playing like that.
You'll be there one day.

915
01:26:26,895 --> 01:26:29,898
- See you around.
- Nice to meet you.

916
01:26:32,276 --> 01:26:36,321
- You know how it is. It's your service.
- Gavino. I just...

917
01:26:37,865 --> 01:26:40,492
Hey. Let me introduce you to my mates.
That's Zizou.

918
01:26:40,576 --> 01:26:42,870
This is Raul.
Santiago Munez.

919
01:26:45,539 --> 01:26:47,708
What the hell are you doing with him?

920
01:26:47,791 --> 01:26:49,334
He's the one with the car.

921
01:26:55,215 --> 01:26:57,176
We have to go.

922
01:26:59,887 --> 01:27:03,807
Take care. Yeah.
See you later. All right. Man.

923
01:27:05,267 --> 01:27:10,272
<i>They're over here shooting a commercial.
Mucho dinero. Santi.</i>

924
01:27:10,355 --> 01:27:14,818
- Come on. Let's go. This place is dead.
- What? What do you mean? Where?

925
01:27:14,902 --> 01:27:16,570
This is my town. Son.

926
01:27:20,783 --> 01:27:25,788
Boys. Wicked. We were gonna
send out a search party for you two.

927
01:27:27,539 --> 01:27:30,209
- Nice party. Man.
- This ain't the party.

928
01:27:30,292 --> 01:27:33,462
- Come on. Follow me.
- Upstairs again.

929
01:27:36,965 --> 01:27:38,717
This is the party.

930
01:27:39,468 --> 01:27:41,011
Hello. Boys.

931
01:27:41,095 --> 01:27:44,139
- Fill your boots. Son. It's your birthday.
- Shame on us.

932
01:27:44,223 --> 01:27:46,892
Get in there.

933
01:27:46,975 --> 01:27:49,853
- We're getting this.
- Excuse me.

934
01:27:49,937 --> 01:27:52,356
Come on. Don't be shy.

935
01:27:53,357 --> 01:27:55,692
Ball control. A bit of ball control.

936
01:27:56,485 --> 01:28:00,572
Don't be shy. Your mother wasn't.
That's it. Get in there.

937
01:28:17,047 --> 01:28:21,677
- Not your kind of party?
- I never know what to say.

938
01:28:21,760 --> 01:28:26,223
You wouldn't need to say anything
to most of the girls in there.

939
01:28:26,306 --> 01:28:30,018
I have a girl.
Well. I think I have one.

940
01:28:31,061 --> 01:28:33,355
I met someone I really like.

941
01:28:33,439 --> 01:28:35,941
She's very lucky.

942
01:28:39,278 --> 01:28:41,363
How did you and Gavino meet?

943
01:28:41,447 --> 01:28:43,490
Party like this.

944
01:28:43,574 --> 01:28:46,076
Much the same people.

945
01:28:46,160 --> 01:28:48,704
Musos. Models. Footballers.

946
01:28:52,166 --> 01:28:55,419
Listen. Don't tell him I've gone.

947
01:28:55,502 --> 01:28:58,005
Not that he'd notice.

948
01:29:04,344 --> 01:29:06,638
Want to explain this?

949
01:29:07,890 --> 01:29:13,020
There's nothing to explain. Sir.
It was just people fooling around at a party.

950
01:29:13,103 --> 01:29:17,274
When you travel with this club.
You're an ambassador for this club.

951
01:29:17,357 --> 01:29:19,401
Mr Dornhelm. It's not my fault.

952
01:29:19,485 --> 01:29:22,738
It is your fault. You exposed yourself
to this kind of situation.

953
01:29:22,821 --> 01:29:24,948
- Who is the other player?
- The other one?

954
01:29:25,032 --> 01:29:28,285
It says there are two Newcastle players.

955
01:29:28,368 --> 01:29:30,454
Who is the other one?

956
01:29:30,537 --> 01:29:34,541
- I cannot tell you that. Sir.
- You mean you won't tell me?

957
01:29:36,543 --> 01:29:38,545
Yeah.

958
01:29:40,339 --> 01:29:43,801
Roz. Roz. Hey.
I have to explain about that picture.

959
01:29:43,884 --> 01:29:45,469
<i>- What picture?
- In The Sun.</i>

960
01:29:45,552 --> 01:29:47,805
- Don't read that rag.
- You haven't seen it?

961
01:29:47,888 --> 01:29:51,308
I showed it to her.
Looked like a good party. That.

962
01:29:51,391 --> 01:29:53,560
Are those lasses' tits real?

963
01:29:54,478 --> 01:29:58,148
- It wasn't how it looked.
- Look. I don't wanna talk about it. OK?

964
01:29:58,232 --> 01:30:02,111
I'm busy. You should go and visit
your friend Jamie while you're here.

965
01:30:02,194 --> 01:30:04,488
He's in examination room B.

966
01:30:10,035 --> 01:30:13,038
- Hey.
- Hey. Santi.

967
01:30:13,122 --> 01:30:17,501
- What happened. Man?
- I got stretchered off in the reserve game.

968
01:30:17,584 --> 01:30:20,587
They've sent me here for an MRI scan.

969
01:30:20,671 --> 01:30:25,092
You'll be fine.
They can fix anything these days. Man.

970
01:30:25,843 --> 01:30:29,638
I don't know.
It felt really bad when it happened.

971
01:30:29,721 --> 01:30:31,890
You could just tell.

972
01:30:34,685 --> 01:30:38,731
I reckon I might have to skip
them salsa lessons.

973
01:30:53,495 --> 01:30:55,831
His meniscus is shattered.

974
01:30:56,623 --> 01:30:59,960
And there's a tear
in the lateral cruciate ligament.

975
01:31:00,043 --> 01:31:02,421
I don't know what that means.

976
01:31:03,088 --> 01:31:05,674
Just tell me. Can he play again?

977
01:31:07,593 --> 01:31:09,928
Not if he wants to walk. No.

978
01:31:19,396 --> 01:31:21,398
- All right. Geezer?
- Hey.

979
01:31:23,400 --> 01:31:25,861
Hey. Man. Thanks
for covering for me. Yeah.

980
01:31:25,944 --> 01:31:29,364
You're a top man. If you fingered me.
I was right in the shitter.

981
01:31:29,448 --> 01:31:33,243
We're even. OK?
I don't owe you no more favours.

982
01:31:34,578 --> 01:31:35,913
OK.

983
01:31:35,996 --> 01:31:39,333
You're screwing up your life. Man.
That's how you lost Christina.

984
01:31:39,416 --> 01:31:42,753
- She'll be back.
- No. She won't. You know why?

985
01:31:42,836 --> 01:31:45,923
'Cause she can't stand
your asshole friends.

986
01:31:46,006 --> 01:31:48,675
How do you think that picture
ends up in the paper?

987
01:31:48,759 --> 01:31:51,053
Bluto sold it.

988
01:31:51,136 --> 01:31:56,517
How much does your buddy make dealing
drugs at all the places you get him into?

989
01:31:56,600 --> 01:31:58,977
Think I'm some greaseball
who doesn't know stuff?

990
01:31:59,061 --> 01:32:02,189
These are the best years of our lives
and how long have we got?

991
01:32:02,272 --> 01:32:05,234
Ten. If we're lucky?
Or even less. If we get hurt like Jamie.

992
01:32:05,317 --> 01:32:11,281
It can happen to any of us. We're one
tackle away from flipping burgers.

993
01:32:15,619 --> 01:32:17,621
Get out.

994
01:32:19,706 --> 01:32:21,667
Go on. Piss off.

995
01:32:40,686 --> 01:32:42,229
Where's Dad?

996
01:32:42,312 --> 01:32:44,982
He's setting the sprinklers.

997
01:32:55,367 --> 01:32:58,370
Come on. Dad. Let's go.

998
01:32:59,288 --> 01:33:00,664
Dad?

999
01:33:11,008 --> 01:33:12,843
Dad.

1000
01:33:15,053 --> 01:33:18,849
Dad. Wake up. Dad.
Dad. Wake up.

1001
01:33:29,193 --> 01:33:31,236
Hey. Glen.

1002
01:33:31,987 --> 01:33:36,158
Hey. I meant to come over and explain
about that thing in the newspaper.

1003
01:33:36,241 --> 01:33:38,869
Santi. I had a call from LA.

1004
01:33:38,911 --> 01:33:42,247
You need to phone your grandmother.

1005
01:33:59,014 --> 01:34:01,517
- Glen. What's happened?
- His father.

1006
01:34:01,600 --> 01:34:03,769
Heart attack. Apparently.

1007
01:34:04,603 --> 01:34:06,897
Is he going to be all right?

1008
01:34:06,980 --> 01:34:09,441
Dead.

1009
01:34:21,370 --> 01:34:23,872
- I've got it.
- No. It's OK. Man.

1010
01:34:24,748 --> 01:34:26,583
Here.

1011
01:34:27,584 --> 01:34:29,586
Thanks for everything.

1012
01:34:32,089 --> 01:34:34,091
Safe journey.

1013
01:34:42,224 --> 01:34:46,228
- Yes. Boss.
- There you go. Brilliant. Thank you.

1014
01:34:46,311 --> 01:34:48,272
Hey. Boss.

1015
01:34:50,274 --> 01:34:52,818
- Can I have a word?
- Yes. Please.

1016
01:34:58,073 --> 01:35:01,702
- I was the other bloke in that picture.
- I'm shocked.

1017
01:35:01,785 --> 01:35:05,122
And I thought you should know...

1018
01:35:06,039 --> 01:35:08,876
it was me that dragged Santi
to that party to begin with.

1019
01:35:08,959 --> 01:35:12,880
He didn't even wanna go.
It's not his scene. He's a good lad.

1020
01:35:12,963 --> 01:35:15,382
I take full responsibility.

1021
01:35:17,259 --> 01:35:20,471
Boys with big bank accounts are still boys.

1022
01:35:21,013 --> 01:35:24,183
This is not an excuse for you any more.

1023
01:35:24,266 --> 01:35:27,186
- You're how old?
- 28.

1024
01:35:28,062 --> 01:35:31,815
- 29. I think.
- Yeah. Around that.

1025
01:35:32,900 --> 01:35:36,028
The young players should
be looking to you for an example.

1026
01:35:36,111 --> 01:35:39,281
Off the field as well as on.
Am I right?

1027
01:35:41,283 --> 01:35:43,994
I hear what you're saying. Boss.

1028
01:35:45,662 --> 01:35:47,331
And...

1029
01:35:48,082 --> 01:35:51,126
you're not the first person to say it.

1030
01:36:00,469 --> 01:36:03,889
Flight 19 to London Heathrow
is now boarding.

1031
01:36:03,972 --> 01:36:09,520
All connecting international flights
will be listed on arrival.

1032
01:36:50,310 --> 01:36:52,938
Sir. We're boarding now.

1033
01:36:57,192 --> 01:37:00,779
Keep stretching. Lads.
It'll be a long day.

1034
01:37:05,242 --> 01:37:09,621
What the hell are you doing here?
Why aren't you on the plane?

1035
01:37:09,705 --> 01:37:13,250
I'm sitting in the airport
and I think to myself.

1036
01:37:13,333 --> 01:37:15,544
At least now I have an excuse.

1037
01:37:15,627 --> 01:37:19,673
A reason to give my buddies and
everybody else why things didn't work out.

1038
01:37:19,757 --> 01:37:24,803
"Hey. My dad died. I had to come home.
Take care of business."

1039
01:37:26,346 --> 01:37:30,142
- Know why I needed an excuse?
- No.

1040
01:37:30,225 --> 01:37:33,270
Because that's the way
my father made me think.

1041
01:37:33,353 --> 01:37:35,397
He took away my self-belief.

1042
01:37:35,481 --> 01:37:39,902
<i>He made it impossible
to have... aspiracion.</i>

1043
01:37:39,985 --> 01:37:43,072
- Aspiration. You understand?
- Yes.

1044
01:37:43,155 --> 01:37:45,324
I don't need an excuse.

1045
01:37:46,366 --> 01:37:50,162
The only person who can tell me
I'm not good enough is you.

1046
01:37:54,333 --> 01:37:56,335
And even then...

1047
01:37:58,796 --> 01:38:01,423
I may not agree with you.

1048
01:38:10,015 --> 01:38:12,017
You are right. Santi.

1049
01:38:13,185 --> 01:38:15,813
There's no point in coming back.

1050
01:38:16,730 --> 01:38:18,732
It's God's will.

1051
01:38:30,619 --> 01:38:32,496
Hey.

1052
01:38:32,579 --> 01:38:33,872
Hi.

1053
01:38:38,752 --> 01:38:41,422
So how are you feeling?

1054
01:38:44,425 --> 01:38:46,718
I never made peace with my dad.

1055
01:38:46,802 --> 01:38:50,389
- He never made peace with you either.
- No. But he never forgave me.

1056
01:38:50,472 --> 01:38:52,474
You don't know that.

1057
01:38:53,308 --> 01:38:55,769
How can you know that?

1058
01:38:55,853 --> 01:38:59,523
What about all those pictures
you sent home?

1059
01:39:00,983 --> 01:39:03,986
I don't know where home is any more.

1060
01:39:04,069 --> 01:39:06,155
Yeah. You do.

1061
01:39:06,238 --> 01:39:10,451
It's green
and it's got a goalpost at each end.

1062
01:39:43,317 --> 01:39:45,319
Munez.

1063
01:39:59,958 --> 01:40:01,960
How are you doing?

1064
01:40:03,545 --> 01:40:06,048
OK. Boss.

1065
01:40:06,131 --> 01:40:10,427
Tough thing to lose a father.
I remember when I lost mine.

1066
01:40:11,512 --> 01:40:12,971
Thank you.

1067
01:40:15,557 --> 01:40:20,187
You shouldn't be here.
The groundsman is having a fit.

1068
01:40:20,270 --> 01:40:22,272
His turf is sacred.

1069
01:40:23,482 --> 01:40:25,150
I just...

1070
01:40:26,151 --> 01:40:28,654
I just wanted to see what it felt like.

1071
01:40:28,737 --> 01:40:31,073
You know...

1072
01:40:31,156 --> 01:40:33,325
to be on this pitch.

1073
01:40:34,576 --> 01:40:37,413
You'll find out Saturday.

1074
01:40:37,496 --> 01:40:39,665
Now get off the grass.

1075
01:40:51,343 --> 01:40:53,011
Yeah.

1076
01:40:59,476 --> 01:41:02,813
I'm in the squad for the Liverpool game.

1077
01:41:04,606 --> 01:41:06,567
- Get us a ticket. Then. Will you?
- Yeah.

1078
01:41:06,650 --> 01:41:09,236
Well done. Son. Well done.

1079
01:41:09,319 --> 01:41:13,699
Well. I never doubted it. Son. First time
I saw you. I said to Phil. Didn't I. Phil?

1080
01:41:13,782 --> 01:41:16,160
- That lad's got it.
- No. You didn't.

1081
01:41:17,953 --> 01:41:20,330
I owe you. Man.
Breakfast. Remember?

1082
01:41:20,414 --> 01:41:22,249
Here.

1083
01:41:22,332 --> 01:41:24,334
Get in. We're celebrating.

1084
01:41:24,418 --> 01:41:26,837
- Is that Gavin Harris?
- Where?

1085
01:41:26,920 --> 01:41:32,259
<i>We're meeting a couple of girls at a club
and then back to my gaff. La vida loca.</i>

1086
01:41:33,051 --> 01:41:36,096
I'm joking. Blockbuster and pizza.

1087
01:41:38,307 --> 01:41:40,309
Can we put the top up?
My ass is freezing.

1088
01:41:40,392 --> 01:41:42,394
Buy a coat.

1089
01:42:11,006 --> 01:42:15,886
It's down to this. The last game.
Against their main rivals. Liverpool.

1090
01:42:15,969 --> 01:42:19,348
The next 90 minutes
will decide Newcastle's fate.

1091
01:42:19,431 --> 01:42:22,768
Will it be Europe. And all the glory
that goes with it. Next season?

1092
01:42:22,851 --> 01:42:25,604
If so. They have to win today.

1093
01:42:29,233 --> 01:42:31,860
Private box?

1094
01:42:31,944 --> 01:42:34,238
I'd check your ticket.

1095
01:42:34,321 --> 01:42:36,490
So. Glen. Are you single then?

1096
01:42:48,127 --> 01:42:50,546
OK. Listen up.

1097
01:42:50,629 --> 01:42:52,631
Guys.

1098
01:43:00,556 --> 01:43:02,891
You know what you have to do.

1099
01:43:40,596 --> 01:43:43,182
Sant's come on. Sant's come on.

1100
01:43:57,529 --> 01:44:01,116
Now. Newcastle are choosing
to start with young Santiago Munez.

1101
01:44:01,200 --> 01:44:04,286
It's only his second-ever appearance
for the senior side.

1102
01:44:04,369 --> 01:44:06,997
I guess they'll be hoping
he produces some of the flair

1103
01:44:07,039 --> 01:44:09,625
that he showed
as a substitute at Fulham last week.

1104
01:44:20,803 --> 01:44:23,222
Our ball.

1105
01:44:23,305 --> 01:44:24,973
Yes.

1106
01:44:25,933 --> 01:44:28,435
- Come on. Sant. Come on. Sant.
- Go. Santiago.

1107
01:44:34,316 --> 01:44:36,527
It is getting physical now.

1108
01:44:36,610 --> 01:44:42,074
You can feel the determination.
Both teams really need this win.

1109
01:44:42,908 --> 01:44:45,202
I've got an airport pickup for you.

1110
01:44:45,285 --> 01:44:50,207
Cannae. Tommy. I'm rushed off me feet.
I'll get back to you.

1111
01:44:53,627 --> 01:44:57,214
Excuse me. Lads.
Room for a little 'un.

1112
01:44:57,297 --> 01:44:59,925
- How's it going?
- We've made all the early running.

1113
01:45:00,008 --> 01:45:02,219
- How long's it been on?
- A minute.

1114
01:45:07,224 --> 01:45:09,476
Given away by Liverpool.

1115
01:45:09,560 --> 01:45:14,565
Alan Shearer looking to organize
a counterattack for Newcastle United.

1116
01:45:15,649 --> 01:45:19,278
He's got support to his right.
Stephen Carr.

1117
01:45:20,863 --> 01:45:23,031
Now Dyer taking over.

1118
01:45:23,115 --> 01:45:26,660
Harris is getting into the middle.
Here comes Harris.

1119
01:45:29,329 --> 01:45:31,331
And a goal. It's Harris.

1120
01:45:32,416 --> 01:45:35,210
It's a dream start for Newcastle.

1121
01:45:36,128 --> 01:45:39,590
And what a way to answer his critics.

1122
01:45:44,094 --> 01:45:46,096
Come on.

1123
01:45:46,930 --> 01:45:49,308
Number ten. Gavin Harris.

1124
01:45:55,773 --> 01:45:57,983
Referee has given the foul.

1125
01:45:59,693 --> 01:46:02,362
Free kick to Liverpool.

1126
01:46:02,780 --> 01:46:05,449
And they've taken it quickly.

1127
01:46:09,620 --> 01:46:11,705
It's a corner.

1128
01:46:13,791 --> 01:46:15,793
Free header.

1129
01:46:17,586 --> 01:46:20,339
Liverpool are level. 1-1.

1130
01:46:20,422 --> 01:46:25,427
Goal-scorer for Liverpool.
Number 25. Igor Biscan.

1131
01:46:32,142 --> 01:46:36,230
Newcastle have given
the ball away yet again.

1132
01:46:39,983 --> 01:46:43,404
Into Baroð.
He's got a chance to shoot here.

1133
01:46:44,113 --> 01:46:47,241
Oh. It's in.
Liverpool lead. 2-1.

1134
01:46:54,665 --> 01:46:58,001
They've conceded two goals
in quick succession without reply.

1135
01:46:58,085 --> 01:47:00,379
That's a devastating blow for Newcastle.

1136
01:47:00,462 --> 01:47:02,840
Now. Can they come back from it?

1137
01:47:05,426 --> 01:47:09,555
Goal-scorer for Liverpool.
Number five. Milan Baroð.

1138
01:47:09,638 --> 01:47:14,518
Here we go. Second half.
With Liverpool firmly in the driving seat.

1139
01:47:14,601 --> 01:47:20,357
And that second goal has really
knocked the stuffing out of the fans.

1140
01:47:24,069 --> 01:47:26,405
Oh. It's a great chance
for Gerrard...

1141
01:47:26,488 --> 01:47:28,741
Oh. So close.

1142
01:47:28,824 --> 01:47:33,537
Had that gone in. It would have been
"Good night. Newcastle."

1143
01:47:39,918 --> 01:47:43,756
Now it's Munez.
The youngster's got some great skill.

1144
01:47:43,839 --> 01:47:47,092
Trying a give-and-go here
with Alan Shearer.

1145
01:47:49,762 --> 01:47:51,847
Give it.

1146
01:47:51,930 --> 01:47:53,140
Pass.

1147
01:47:53,223 --> 01:47:55,142
Give it.

1148
01:47:57,061 --> 01:47:59,438
- Yes.
- Come on. Pass.

1149
01:48:02,649 --> 01:48:04,151
Pass.

1150
01:48:07,863 --> 01:48:10,783
It's a goal. It is 2-2.

1151
01:48:11,784 --> 01:48:13,994
You beauty.

1152
01:48:26,173 --> 01:48:29,802
- We should have a talk about your lad.
- Talk about what. Barry?

1153
01:48:29,885 --> 01:48:33,222
Representation. It's gonna be
a feeding frenzy. Gonna be murders.

1154
01:48:33,305 --> 01:48:37,267
- A lot of sharks out there.
- I know. That's why he signed with me.

1155
01:48:37,351 --> 01:48:38,936
You what?

1156
01:48:39,478 --> 01:48:41,605
Great effort by Newcastle.

1157
01:48:41,688 --> 01:48:48,362
But remember. If it stays like this. It will still
be Liverpool in Europe next season.

1158
01:48:49,571 --> 01:48:53,409
Only three minutes to go now
and Newcastle are running out of time.

1159
01:48:53,492 --> 01:48:58,122
They've got to try
and find a winner from somewhere.

1160
01:48:58,205 --> 01:48:59,623
Back. Come on.

1161
01:49:05,170 --> 01:49:06,922
Come on. Come on. Come on.

1162
01:49:10,676 --> 01:49:13,178
Go on. Son. Have a poke.

1163
01:49:13,971 --> 01:49:15,472
Let go.

1164
01:49:20,561 --> 01:49:23,397
Free kick here.
In a very dangerous area.

1165
01:49:23,480 --> 01:49:25,733
- Get him off.
- Took him down. Give him a card.

1166
01:49:25,816 --> 01:49:30,988
A real chance for Newcastle. This.
But who's going to take it?

1167
01:49:33,031 --> 01:49:35,200
Hey. Santi.

1168
01:49:37,161 --> 01:49:38,245
It's yours.

1169
01:49:38,328 --> 01:49:42,875
I hope they know what they're doing.
It's young Santiago Munez stepping up.

1170
01:49:42,958 --> 01:49:45,669
With only seconds left to play.

1171
01:49:45,753 --> 01:49:52,134
And he must feel that the hopes of
an entire city are resting on his shoulders.

1172
01:50:00,726 --> 01:50:02,853
Come on. Come on. Come on.

1173
01:50:39,181 --> 01:50:42,518
- And I thought you didn't even like football.
- I know.

1174
01:50:42,601 --> 01:50:47,314
Unbelievable.
Newcastle's newest and youngest player

1175
01:50:47,398 --> 01:50:50,567
gives the fans a brand-new song to sing.

1176
01:50:50,651 --> 01:50:55,322
<i>Santiago. Santiago. Ole. Ole. Ole.</i>

1177
01:50:59,118 --> 01:51:02,204
That's my grandson. His brother.

1178
01:51:02,287 --> 01:51:05,207
- It's true. And he's from here.
- We met his dad.

1179
01:51:05,290 --> 01:51:06,875
How could you?

1180
01:51:06,959 --> 01:51:10,838
He was here for the Fulham game. Me
darlin'. He was over the moon. Wasn't he?

1181
01:51:10,921 --> 01:51:12,923
Dad was here?

1182
01:51:16,677 --> 01:51:21,223
Only seconds to go.
Time almost up.

1183
01:51:46,457 --> 01:51:48,125
Santi.

1184
01:51:48,208 --> 01:51:51,545
Santi. Someone wants to speak to you.

1185
01:51:53,589 --> 01:51:54,590
Yeah?

1186
01:51:54,673 --> 01:51:58,927
Santiago. Santiago. We saw the game.

1187
01:51:59,011 --> 01:52:01,305
Julio and me.

1188
01:52:01,388 --> 01:52:06,060
No. Glen's daughter brought us.
You were fantastic.

1189
01:52:06,643 --> 01:52:10,647
<i>Si. And I wanna tell you something else.
About your father.</i>

1190
01:52:13,150 --> 01:52:15,694
Hey. Glen.

1191
01:52:16,779 --> 01:52:20,657
You know when I played against Fulham?

1192
01:52:20,741 --> 01:52:22,743
My dad saw the game.

1193
01:52:24,203 --> 01:52:26,580
He saw me play. Man.

1194
01:52:27,289 --> 01:52:30,125
He's probably watching you right now.

1195
01:52:34,546 --> 01:52:36,757
Santi.

1196
01:52:36,840 --> 01:52:38,550
Santi.

1197
01:52:38,634 --> 01:52:40,636
Santiago.

1198
01:52:48,102 --> 01:52:50,104
Yeah.

